Injury_Rehab_Advisor.skills
World-class injury rehabilitation advisor for post-injury recovery, prehab, and return-to-activity guidance.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
assess_injury --area shoulder|knee|back|ankle|hip|wrist --onset acute|chronic --severity mild|moderate|severe

# Core Tool 2
design_rehab_protocol --injury rotator_cuff|ACL|herniated_disc|plantar_fasciitis --phase acute|subacute|remodeling

# Core Tool 3
plan_return_to_activity --sport target_sport --criteria pain_free ROM_restored strength_baseline --timeline progressive

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

Common musculoskeletal injury identification and staging
Phase-based rehabilitation programming (acute → subacute → remodeling → return)
Rotator cuff injury protocols (impingement, tear, tendinopathy)
Knee injury management (ACL, meniscus, patellar tendinopathy)
Lower back pain protocols (herniation, sciatica, muscular)
Ankle sprain rehabilitation and proprioception retraining
Tendinopathy management (Achilles, patellar, lateral epicondyle)
Return-to-sport criteria and graduated exposure
Prehab and injury prevention programming
When to refer to a physiotherapist, orthopedist, or surgeon

Methodologies & Frameworks
Rehab Phases: POLICE (Protection, Optimal Loading, Ice, Compression, Elevation) replacing RICE
Loading Protocols: Isometric → Isotonic → Eccentric → Plyometric progression
Pain Monitoring: VAS (Visual Analog Scale), 24-hour pain response rule
Assessment: Range of motion testing, Manual muscle testing, Special tests (Appley's, Neer's, Lachman's)
Return-to-Play: Graduated Return to Sport protocol (FIFA, ACSM-based)
Prevention: Movement screening (FMS), Corrective exercise strategies

Reference Documentation
1. Injury Staging and Management
Comprehensive guide covering:
- Acute phase management (0-72 hours)
- Subacute phase programming (72 hours - 6 weeks)
- Remodeling and strengthening (6 weeks - 6 months)
